indicator_01.description: Based on the demand from the states / UTs funds are made available by the Union Government for the scheme.
indicator_01.name: Total Available Fund
indicator_01.note: Total Available Fund includes Opening Balance as per Utilisation Certificate.

indicator_02.description: Total expenditure incurred on wage payments to labourers
indicator_02.name: Total Expenditure on Wages
indicator_02.note: Does not include material cost, administrative expenditure or tax payments

indicator_03.description: Total expenditure incurred on procuring materials
indicator_03.name: Total Expenditure on Materials
indicator_03.note: Does not include wage payments, administrative expenditure or tax payments

indicator_04.description: Aggregate expenditure on wage, materials, admin & tax
indicator_04.name: Grand Total Expenditure

indicator_05.description: The total unspent balance is the difference between the total available fund and grand total expenditure (including payment due).
indicator_05.name: Total Unspent Balance
indicator_05.note: Negative balance indicates the unspent balance available with the States / UTs

indicator_06.description: This measures the extent of fund utilised out of the funds available under the scheme
indicator_06.name: Extent of Fund Utilisation
indicator_06.note: This is computed by taking the total fund available upon the total expenditure (including payment due) multiplied by 100. More than 100 per cent fund utilisation indicates negative net fund balance under the scheme budget

metadata.description: MGNREGS aims to enhance livelihood security of the rural masses with a provision of at least 100 days of wage employment in a financial year to every rural household whose adult member volunteers to do unskilled manual work. This is one of the world’s largest public sector employment programmes, providing guaranteed income through employment.
metadata.name: Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Scheme
metadata.source: Aggregated by CBGA & CDL based on MIS data
